---

<section class='about' id='about'>
  <div class='container fade-in'>
    <div class='section-label'>About</div>
    <div class='about-content'>
      <div class='about-text'>
        <p>
          I began working with stringed instruments in the 1980s doing repair work for local music
          stores where close, hands-on work with well-used instruments built a practical
          understanding of materials, structure and feel.
        </p>
        <p>
          Today, tone, balance, and volume guide every guitar I build, shaping an expressive,
          resonant voice. A gently elevated neck with a subtle twist and an evenly carved profile
          create a natural, comfortable feel in the hand. Carefully chosen woods and details give
          each instrument a visual character that reflects its sound. I build only a few guitars
          each year. Classical guitars are my main focus but I enjoy building steel stringed guitars
          as well. No matter what I build, each is crafted to inspire creativity and bring the simple
          pleasure of playing.
        </p>
        <p class='signature'>— David Ryer</p>
      </div>
      <img
        class='about-img'
        src='/images/workshop.jpeg'
        alt='David Ryer guitar workshop in Madoc, Ontario'
        fetchpriority='high'
        decoding='async'
      />
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .about {
    background: var(--bg-warm);
  }
  .about-content {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: stretch;
  }
  .about-text {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: center;
  }
  .about-text p {
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
    color: var(--cream-dim);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
  .about-text .signature {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }
  .about-img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    filter: grayscale(20%) contrast(1.05);
    border: 1px solid rgba(201, 169, 110, 0.15);
    background: var(--bg-card);
    display: block;
    min-height: 300px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 1024px) and (min-width: 901px) {
    .about-content {
      grid-template-columns: 1.3fr 0.7fr;
      gap: 2rem;
    }
  }
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .about-content {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    .about-img {
      height: auto;
      aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;
      width: 100%;
      min-height: unset;
    }
  }
</style>
